| **Category**                | **Tools/Libraries**                        |
| --------------------------- | ------------------------------------------ |
| **Programming Language**    | Python 3.7 or later                        |
| **Data Manipulation**       | Pandas, NumPy                              |
| **Visualization**           | Matplotlib, Seaborn                        |
| **Statistical Modeling**    | Statsmodels (for ARIMA, SARIMA)            |
| **Machine Learning**        | Scikit-learn (for ML models)               |
| **Deep Learning**           | TensorFlow, Keras, PyTorch (for LSTM, CNN) |
| **Time Series Forecasting** | Darts (for unified time series models)     |
| **Database**                | InfluxDB (for time series data storage)    |
| **Development Environment** | Jupyter Notebook, VS Code, PyCharm         |



| **Data Type**           | **Description**                                                                              |
| ----------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Energy Consumption**  | Time-stamped data on energy usage (e.g., hourly, daily)                                      |
| **Weather Data**        | Temperature, humidity, wind speed, etc., affecting energy demand                             |
| **Calendar Data**       | Information on holidays, weekends, and seasons                                               |
| **Economic Indicators** | Data on industrial activity, population, and economic factors influencing energy consumption |
| **Data Sources**        | Smart meters, weather APIs, government databases, utility companies, and open datasets       |




| **Aspect**              | **Details**                                                                        |
| ----------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Data Preprocessing**  | Handling missing values, outlier detection, normalization, and feature engineering |
| **Modeling Techniques** | ARIMA, SARIMA, LSTM, Prophet, Hybrid models                                        |
| **Evaluation Metrics**  | RMSE, MAE, MAPE, RÂ²                                                                |
| **Cross-Validation**    | Time series cross-validation techniques (e.g., walk-forward validation)            |
| **Model Deployment**    | Flask/Django APIs, cloud services (AWS SageMaker, Google AI Platform)              |


| **Component**        | **Tools/Technologies**                    |
| -------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| **Database**         | InfluxDB (optimized for time series data) |
| **Cloud Platforms**  | AWS, Google Cloud, Azure                  |
| **Version Control**  | Git, GitHub/GitLab                        |
